entry.tran: 不吸引人的；其貌不扬的
entry.def: If you describe someone or something as unprepossessing, you mean that they look rather plain or ordinary, although they may have good or special qualities that are hidden.

example.ex: We found the tastiest and most imaginative paella and tapas in the most unprepossessing bars and cafés.
example.tran: 我们在最不起眼的酒吧和咖啡馆找到了最可口、最具创意的肉菜饭和餐前小吃。
